author: Inside Edition
description: A police officer found a home in flames. His bodycam footage captured the inferno and the chilling cries coming from inside. Auburn, New York, Officer Paul Flickner and a deputy sheriff successfully helped the victim escape through the window.
title: Bodycam Shows House Fire Rescue #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Four-year-old Ronan Kerr was with his dad, Cathal, and 7-year-old brother when a 27-foot-long eucalyptus tree branch crashed down. The dad was knocked unconscious and suffered multiple injuries. Ronan was rushed to the hospital with a traumatic brain injury. Seven days later, Ronan died. The parents tell Inside Edition they fear that the same horror could happen to another family. They are now suing the city of San Diego and the two contractors that were hired to care for the tree.
title: Family Sues San Diego After Fallen Tree Branch Kills 4-Year-Old Boy

author: Inside Edition
description: Ally of President Donald Trump Megyn Kelly called on the president to release the Epstein files. Pressure is mounting after a trove of 23,000 emails and other Jeffrey Epstein documents put Trump's relationship with the convicted pedophile in a new light. Epstein and Trump were once close friends but they had a falling out. The White House is reportedly pressuring Republicans to vote against releasing the Epstein Files.
title: Pressure Mounts On President Trump To Release Epstein Files

author: Inside Edition
description: A surfer was attacked by a shark and lived to tell the tale. Andy McDonald says he was enjoying a day of windsurfing on the Margaret River in Australia when he was rudely interrupted. The fight for his life was captured on video, but it's unclear what was happening. Other windsurfers got closer trying to see what was going on. McDonald was lucky to escape with his life, and even luckier to be completely uninjured after fighting off the shark. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Surfer Loses A Board But Survives Shark Attack In Australia

author: Inside Edition
description: Michelino Sunseri was trying to set a record for running to the top of Grand Teton Peak in Wyoming and back down. But, he took a trail that the National Park Service has label restricted. Sunseri found himself criminally charged with violating park service regulations. He tells Inside Edition he was found guilty and faced penalties of up to $5,000 or six months in jail. An uproar ensued and President Donald Trump stepped in. Sunseri got a presidential pardon.
title: Accused Runner Gets Presidential Pardon After Taking Restricted Path

author: Inside Edition
description: The family of an 18-year-old high school senior who died under mysterious circumstances on a cruise ship in the Caribbean is breaking their silence. Anna Kepner's grieving father, Christopher, says he is desperate for answers. Anna died on the Carnival ship "Horizon" at 11:17 a.m. according to the Miami-Dade medical examiner. Instead of flowers for the funeral, friends were encouraged to leave flowers on Anna's car, which is parked at her high school outside Orlando where she last left it.
title: Family Of Teen Who Died On Carnival Cruise Ship Breaks Their Silence

author: Inside Edition
description: A much-hyped humanoid robot made its Moscow debut this week. When AIDOL appeared from the wings, it had a stomping kind of gait. AIDOL made its way to the front of the stage, waving to the crowd, and then face-planted. AIDOL's human helpers rushed to its aid, while someone tried to pull a black curtain to hide the AI fail. Afterwards, the CEO of the tech company behind AIDOL told Russian media he hoped "this mistake will turn into an experience."
title: Russian AI Robot Faceplants

author: Inside Edition
description: While these cops saw their chase coming to an end, the suspect still had hope of getting away. This happened in Royal Oak, Michigan. Police say they attempted to talk to the driver, who was parked near some train tracks and had an open container of alcohol in her vehicle. They say she refused to talk to them and drove off, which kicked off this chase. After crashing into the Ulta beauty, the suspect still wasn't ready to surrender. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspect Destroys Ulta Beauty Store After Crashing Into It During Police Chase

author: Inside Edition
description: A growing number of women are taking testosterone. Mom of four Alixa Winn started injecting testosterone when she was 35. She tells Inside Edition that she got a boost in energy within months of taking it. Angie Knierm, 54, takes testosterone in a topical cream. Initially, she ended up taking too high a dose and had symptoms similar to roid rage. New Jersey urologist Dr. Anika Ackerman says taking the right dose is key.
title: Growing Number Of Women Are Taking Testosterone

author: Inside Edition
description: At 76 years old, Janet Fontaine walked down the aisle for the first time. Waiting at the altar was her 81-year-old groom, Cliff. Janet says over her many decades of life, she's dated lots of guys, but nothing ever clicked.
title: 76-Year-Old Woman Gets Married For First Time #shorts
